caption: One of my favorite breakfast/brunch spots.  This has been an excellent addition to Bowie Town Center!
Overall it was ok.
Went there for the first time yesterday with a group of friends, food was cold and bland. Nothing special about First Watch despite their extensive menu.
Pancakes, chickichanga, Florida French toast. Food was good.

So sick of this First Watch. Started out well when it first opened but now have had 2 back to back poor experiences. Tried the online ordering through the app and they lost the order. Then today we used the “Get in Line” function on the app at 10:00am. It told us when to arrive to the restaurant - 11:05am. We arrive and the hostess tells us that the wait will be another 45 minutes. When we expressed our frustration we were told that it’s out of her control and nothing we can do. Then after her poor explanation asked if what she was saying “made sense”? I told her it did not and then the cashier jumped in as well to say it was out of their control. My whole thing: FIX IT! Poor experiences all around from dealing with their ridiculous application to their patronizing hostess and cashier.
We found our local place!
Taste and great service healthy food
This place is worth trying. They have big portions for convenient rates. Consistently well kept and with good atmosphere. Highly recommended.
Waited for more than an hour because the wait list said so. After an hour an a half they told us we had to wait another hour. They just don't appear ready to serve the public. Poor management skills

The food was so good and the general vibe of the place was gorgeous and peaceful even though they were busy.  Waitress was amazing and attentive.  I had the French toast and maple bacon. I can't wait to visit again.  I felt safe eating there.

My wife and I went to get some brunch yesterday well that was the plan but when we arrived and went in to put our name in the waiting list we were told it was going to take 45 to 50 mins wait that was at 11:43 am we waited in our car at 12:30 I went back to checked sino it has been 45 minutes the lady at host stand was very rude and unpleasant when I ask about my reservation and she was well we told is going to be 45 to 60 minutes and looks like it going be more like the 60 minutes. We got tired and hungry we left and I end up getting a text about our table been ready at 1:15 pm. After we have already gone to another places to eat.

If I could give it zero stars I would! I went online and joined waitlist. Got there at 5 till 1100. Went inside to determine how long. Lady said you checked in at 1104 and I had been ther 17 mins and that it would be about 25 mins. At 1145 I went inside and asked how long as it had been 45 mins already. Lady said there were 2 more in front of me still and that tables were taking longer and they had no idea how long it would be.  Website and lady said 45 mins from when I booked, yet it would have been closer to an hour! I give a lot of restaurants grace during COVID, but this was totally UNACCEPTABLE!!  DO NOT GO HERE AS THEIR CUSTOMER SERVICE SUCKS!
Great food and good service.  I love coming to eat there
Luis is the man! Came here with a friend and the service was absolutely amazing, along with the food. Will be back!
Fabulous food fabulous portion sizes absolutely excellent I can't wait till covid-19 so we can all sit down and really enjoy the wonderful service I know that your company provides
The food here is great! Atmosphere and service at thw Bowie Town Center location is awesome!
DELICIOUS and service is GREAT. Awesome, expansive menu (brunch) and everything i ate was simply, just really good. A+
Food and service was outstanding.

This place is great. I also like how everyone helps each other out. I’ve seen a manager bus a table and I’ve seen a busser grab extra creamers for a guest at a table. Love the teamwork and OF COURSE the food. The million dollar bacon is the greatest invention ever made
Excellent food no complaints

Mmm breakfast! You can tell everything is fresh! Even the orange juice. Tastes amazing. Ice had different breakfast dishes and they've all be amazing. If you order anything besides breakfast it is a hit or miss, but still decent nonetheless. Great local breakfast place. Better than the Bob Evans down the street.
First watch is one of thee best breakfast places around. Always great food and great service.  It might always be a line to get in but it's worth it

First Watch has good food, but their “online ordering system” is terrible. I usually use a third party app like Door Dash to order my food, but I decided to order directly from the site this time. When I went to pay, a message stating “the restaurant is at capacity and would no longer be accepting orders” pops up. First Watch cancelled my order and said a refund would be sent out in 7-10 business days. The “live” feature on Google said the restaurant wasn’t busy, so I was confused.  I tried Door Dash to make sure it wasn’t just their site, but I got the same results. So, I decided to call the restaurant, and the employee that answered said they weren’t taking orders over the phone... try the website. I explained what was happening, but I already knew there was nothing she could do about it. I guess this location is short staffed or something to shut down ALL online ordering and all I ordered was two sides and a muffin. S/n: This isn’t the first online issue I’ve had; it’s why I called just to check.

Best breakfast I had in a LONG time. The fried potatoes omg perfection. The french toast was HUGE. The OJ oh yea baby that didn't come from nobodies carton. Even the fruit that I stole off my husbands plate hit different. I cant wait to go back. Social distancing regulations are implemented so you might have a little wait for a table but a trip to the DT next door knocked that out for me
Very friendly staff and delicious food.

We enjoy eating out. Last night we arrived in this fine place which we didn’t know before. We had a beautiful evening there with superb dishes and a nice stuff and  a professional chief cook. We put this restaurant in our phone list  and we shall definitely come back soon. We warmly recommend.
The food was great. The place is simple and service was good.
The  environment is a win. It's very urban and clean space. The entree section is so cost efficient and a great add to the overall larger options.

Even though there was a 45-60 minute wait today and I wasn't allowed to make a to-go order because it was only available online....... I still give this place five Stars .... simply because the food is outstanding 🎇🎆 and the service 🏅 is great! I like their granola pancakes and avocado toast..... I will return...

My request was clearly stated on the receipt taped to the bag! This week, I got no toast at all (plenty of butter though). The omelettes are great, it’s just a shame they don’t pay more attention to what they’re doing. Especially since they ask for a tip up front when ordering.
I eat here a lot since I work nearby. I love how their customer service is always excellent and they keep the place neat regularly. Rates are fair and they serve generous portions.
Food and hospitality were beyond compare. Really great job!
I just love this place, it's people and the food is great
Ordered take out, everything was complete as requested.  Quality food. Our go-to spot for breakfast/lunch.
Love it especially the fiid fresh always, love Live their eggs n bacon
The food the staff and environment is great.

We went to First Watch in Bowie and it was very very well run. The Hostess at the front gave estimated sitting time and was more then friendly and polite. We were sifted and almost immediately our waitress (Dis) greeted us. Dis gave us any information we asked. She went out of her way to make this visit very pleasant. My cudos to the manager for such a well run establishment.Would go back anytime eventhough I live in Annapolis.
A little slow but food is always good

Not happy with this place. I put my name on the waiting lists to eat in, the girl said 15 to 20 minutes wait. That's 15 to 20 minutes turn to 1 hours. If they know its a long wait they should let people knows right up front so we decided to still wait or go somewhere. Their food is ok, but its not that serious to wait for hours and then wait another 45 minutes to bring your food. They definitely don't care.
The service left a lot to be desired

Used to go here on weekends in the "before times" and the waits were very long, about 30-45 minutes, but the food was delicious, so I was satisfied. I like any of their food with avocado in it, it was always fresh, and their iced coffee is great. My recent problem is that they advertise that you can get delivery through Doordash but it will show their restaurant as closed on the app at random times throughout the week, so I can't order even right as they open in the morning. I've tried calling the restaurant and they say they turn it off or on depending on how busy they are--which seems weird because they're a business, don't they want to make money?  Anyways, I still recommend them for the good variety of breakfast/lunch foods, but hope they can figure out the delivery issue.
The food is fantastic.

Great breakfast. Small glitches: made a point to be sure the egg whites were cooked on my poached eggs Benedict Florentine. Bread was great, spinach beautiful skimpy on the hollandaise, but ONLY got egg whites, no yolk.  She didn't check back so I couldn't say anything. My guy had biscuits and turkey gravy... Was wonderful.

Disappointed! We were very excited to be able to order via Uber Eats. It was finally available in our area. I ordered 3 meals....only received one bag which was labeled 2 of 2. After waiting over an hour, the bag that came was not my order and the food was not what I was expecting. When I called the restaurant to speak with the Manager, my complaint was not taken well. I wanted them to check to see if the 1 of 2 bag was left there by mistake. I hung up after being on hold.  My family ate everything but the burned biscuit. We did receive a refund from Uber Eats.  I’m sure this was a one time incident as I have been there a few times and very satisfied.

Four of us got four different meals. All were fabulous! Million Dollar Bacon and Donut Holes are a MUST to share before the main course. Morning Meditation drink is really good too! Service is outstanding, but we did have to wait awhile for a table. Believe me, it was worth the wait!
Server too long to come back to our table for the creamer and sugar to go with the coffee ordered.
Great breakfast restaurant and my server, Abby was really good!  I had the lemon ricotta pancakes and I would definitely get them again!!!
Excellent food & coffee!

Ordered 8/9 12:03pm  The overall experience here is not one that is unfamiliar. I've given this place three opportunities before I made my assessment of their general character. I've been a repeat customer here and today will definitely be my last.  The manager with the forehead and the glasses (I believe Ken is the name) is usually the one managing the Sunday's I come in and it has been consistently terrible each time. From unreasonable wait times (1 hour+ when told 25-30 minutes) to incomplete or messy packaging (throwing the food on top of the condiment cups causing them to bust open all over the food), there seems to be no competence at this store. I say the store because every employee I've interacted with has been nonchalant and disengaged.  I attempted several times to address this with Ken but neither he or anyone else responded.  I've found Milk and Honey Cafe and Keith & Son's as better alternatives. More options, can manage a weekend rush, and has higher quality meat options.
The food was amazing.
Good was delicious

We decided to order takeout for breakfast to celebrate our 1 year anniversary. Unfortunately when we got home we realized that we were missing a large part of our order. I called to request a refund for the items we did not receive. The manager said that he couldn’t give me a refund unless I came back to the store and that he apologized but there was nothing he could do. Very disappointing customer service.
Great way to start your morning, with a hearty breakfast! Power Pesto Chicken and Quinoa!

I ordered from Uber eats flavor was decent. I ordered the farmhouse hash with over easy eggs. The egg white wasn't cooked. It was clear and slimy, over easy means fully cooked egg white and runny yoke. Please talk to the chef. Preperation and fast, presentation was mediocre. Definitely not worth $13.
Great breakfast

The food is great but every time we decide to dine here, we have to wait at least an hour to be seated and then another 30 to actually receive our food. This is a consistent thing that I thought should be addressed.

Loved it. We were seated quickly and the food came out fast even though they were busy. Everything was absolutely delicious and the prices were on par with what you'd pay at IHOP. The food was really amazing. We all wished our stomachs were bigger so we could order more!
I just enjoyed their dishes. I always get excellent customer service here. The place is well organised and the employees are always nice. Highly recommended.
This spot has amazing service and tasty menu. The best spot in town. The food came out quickly and the prices were reasonable. Highly recommended.
Came here Sunday for brunch, wait was extremely long (over an hour) and it seemed like people who checked in after our party were seated first. However food was decent and the server was really nice.

This place is over rated. We waited over an hour for poor service, below average food.  My food (pancake, bacon and eggs) had long hair in it went arrived to the table; never should have made it out the kitchen. No quality control. NOT recommended!

Members of our party go to other First Watch locations  so they recommended we stop for a family brunch.  arrived at 10:30am, did not recieve food until 11:30am.  pancakes/waffles were cool, cool enough the butter would stick to it. Not a chance of melting!  Should have not been so "PG" and gone to bob evans/dennys etc.  I had the steak hash which was good. Out of six, two of us was satisfied.  Never and i mean never again...
Wow. Go!!!

Brought the office here for breakfast and we were not disappointed. We were satisfied with the quality of the food and service. We will definitely be back for more. A little more expensive than IHOP ,but well worth the value.

I absolutely love this place. I just wish they would stay open later because sometimes my lunch schedule pushes way past 2pm. Johnathan who works in the kitchen is the best, I remember he helped me with something very important a little while back after his shift was done and I still remember how nice and polite he was.
Really liked the atmosphere, kinda hipster-y but in a good way.
Good food, all fresh. Several dishes that were unique that we'll try next time! Service is excellent!!!

The food is good, but not worth the over-extended and inconsiderate wait times; especially if you're on borrowed time. We've frequented this spot many times since moving to Upper Marlboro, MD five plus years ago. It's very popular. However, we've also watched the wait times increase drastically at this location over the years.  The last straw for us occurred right before the holidays. We called ahead to get on the list (they use an app). We were traveling from an early morning appointment in Laurel. Easily a 40-45 min trip.  By the time we arrived, we were still at least 12th in line.  So we waited another 30+ minutes to be seated. After we were seated, we waited for the waiter (another 10-15 min). Placed our drink orders and also ordered appetizers and our main courses (hoping to speed things up). We received our drinks 5-10 min later, and politely asked the waiter if we could eat within the hour, because we had an important appointment at noon (current time, 10:45).  Now granted she respectfully said she wasn't sure we could eat that quickly, we did offer the option of taking it to go if we weren't eating by 11:15. Then we waited.  At 11:15, no food or waiter.  At 11:25, we asked another waiter to call our waiter. Then we asked if the food was ready and relayed that we needed it to go.  She responded that it was almost ready and would prepare to go bags (current time, 11:35). We then explained our concern given how long we'd been waiting (almost an hour just for food...including our appetizers). Her response was that it's not the kitchen or the wait staff, it's the fact that customers don't leave after they eat, instead they continue to occupy a table until they want to leave.  And further, that this is an ongoing issue that management has been trying to figure out how to deal with. As soon as she said this...my wife and I looked at each other.  I knew we were thinking the same thing...this still doesn't explain why it took so long to get our food (or at least appetizers), especially if the restaurant is already aware of the fact that wait times to be seated are extremely long.  This is why we feel the wait time was inconsiderate and therefore have decided to find other options, even if we have to travel further...because after a total wait time of 2.5hrs (from Laurel to being seated and receiving our food in Bowie), there's no doubt we'll actually be able receive our food faster, anywhere else.
Really great food I have to get back here 🤤
I honestly like the food and service, great location nearby to my home. The workers are always very kind. I highly recommend this place.
Love the food. And service... wait time is too long 😑😑
Food was absolutely great. Took a while for the food to come out, but it tasted great. Went for breakfast.
Food was exellent

My husband and I went to the Bowie location for breakfast (4/29/18). We we're greeted with a hostess with a huge frown. It was like she didn't want to be there or we we're a burden. We took our seats at the table and continued to sit there for 10 minutes with no one greeting us. My husband and I noticed that there were about 5-6 servers just standing around in the corner talking. Anyone of them could have came to our table to greet and give us some water. Never again will we go back.  EDIT: I emailed the replay below and huge shocker...no one emailed me back. I have let all my friends know to never step foot inside First Watch.
Wait area never has someone cause they keep going back and forth. Usually gets order wrong and the wait is way to long.
Food is great be prepared to wait.
I was very pleased with the food and service. It's such a relaxing atmosphere  and a great place to telework 😊 The temperature on the inside is always comfortable despite the weather outside.

They have the best customer service!!!!! Their management is awesome, I believe we worked with Danielle and she was phenomenal!!!!! And our sever RJ took great care of us!!!! Plus the food is sooo good!!!

As far as breakfast goes, First Watch is always a great option. The the food here is great. I usually get the break tacos here. However, I have tried plenty of other things that are pretty good. The staff Is very welcoming and friendly. My only complain about this location is how slow they can be when it comes to serving food. It can also get very busy at times with 60+ minute wait times. Besides the wait, the food at this location is easily five stars. It is worth the wait. The last time that I visited this place, my breakfast tacos were hard. The waitress corrected my issue immediately. If you plan to go to this restaurant often, make sure to sign up for the rewards program, as they give a birthday credit towards the final bill. Delicious food! Great ambiance! Disappointed initially with not being welcomed upon entering this establishment; however, another server went above and beyond to make up for that mishap, and the manager came over to apologize. Other than that, this is a magnificent place to dine!
Favirute breakfast spot

The food is FRESH and you can taste the difference in the quality. The service is always EXCELLENT!  I'm about to go now on my day off! Can't wait.. and I'm very picky.. they've never disappointed me!
This place is one of my favorite breakfast spots. The banana crunch pancakes are a hit.

Being a first time visitor I think it was a fairly decent place to eat breakfast. I enjoyed the million dollar bacon, chorizo omelette,  and the carrot cake pecan pancakes. Visited First Watch Bowie today (Sunday). The only thing that saved the visit was the waitstaff (Kelly) and a pleasant young lady from the front whose name I didn’t get. After being told there was a 25min to an hour wait, we decided to stay. A friend had invited me and I wanted to check it out. Close to 2 hours later, I was perplexed why some people seemed to be literally forgotten about. After checking with the woman at the check-in desk a couple of times inquiring when we would be seated, I learned you can request advance seating via the First Watch app.  When finally called to sit, we were seated at a corner booth next to the kitchen.  There were little insects all over the walls and decor above the booth.  We immediately asked to be seated elsewhere.  An employee said the booth had been closed off before due to the same issue. After being reseated, we waited another 15 mins for waitstaff to come to the table.  At this point, we were ready to go.  Kelly asked why we were leaving, we explained how disappointed we had been so far.  Kelly apologized and asked us to stay.  She promised to make sure the kitchen expedited our food quickly. The problem seems to be there is no formula to work in walk-ins so you end up sitting for ridiculous periods of time while the folks using the app get first preference.  This is totally unfair if you 1) have never been to First Watch before or 2) don’t know about the app.  We arrived at 11:15am and weren’t seated until after 1pm.  I realize we didn’t have to wait but others may want to know it isn’t worth going on weekends unless you use the app before going.  The food was overshadowed by the horrendous experience.

I used the First Watch app to secure a wait time of 12:35 today, showed up at the appropriate time, and waited another 10 minutes to be seated. However, as my party was being seated, the other host seated another customer at our table, although our host apologized for the mistake he forgot about us.  We waited another 10 minutes, after which I had to remind the host station that I was still waiting for another table. After being seated, we ordered drinks, which were delivered rather quickly. After receiving our drinks, we ordered breakfast for the table and waited 50 minutes for the food or an explanation from any staff member to explain the delay in our food, but received nothing. After 50 minutes, I asked our server about our meal and she mentioned that it was about to be delivered to the table. Due to the long wait I asked for the meals to be packaged to go as we had another engagement at 3pm. Unfortunately, we waited another 10 minutes for the to-go packages. Opening our to-go bag on the road, we realized that only one meal was in our bag. Instead of the Huevos Rancheros that we ordered, we received a small box of lettuce instead. The overall experience was rather poor and embarrassing as I tried to impress the service and quality of food on my guest. While I will still patron First Watch restaurants, I will not be returning to this one.
